# Hooks

Two groups: **shared** (workspace-wide, import from `@shared/...`) and
**per-app** (defined inside a specific app's `src/hooks/` and tied to its
behavior тАФ auth, permission model, error UX).

Rule: before adding a new hook, grep both tables below for a match. Agents
that add a duplicate hook get a Major finding in review.

## Shared тАФ `@shared/utils/hooks`

Cross-app utilities. Same behavior in every app.

| Hook | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `useRowNavigation` | Click handler for table row тЖТ detail page navigation |
| `useTabUrl` | Syncs active tab with URL search params |
| `useDebounce` | Debounces a value (used by DataTable search) |
| `useFileUpload` | File upload with progress tracking |
| `useDeferredUpload` | Deferred upload (after form submit) |
| `useCountdownTimer` | Countdown (OTP resend, etc.) |
| `useUnsavedChanges` | Warn on navigating away from unsaved form |
| `useSidebar` | Sidebar open/close state |
| <fill>             | <fill> |

## Per-app тАФ `@/hooks` (inside each app)

App-specific hooks. Behavior may differ per app (e.g. `useQueryError` in
admin renders `ForbiddenPage`; in client it toasts). Always import via the
local `@/hooks` alias, not from a sibling app.

| Hook | App | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `usePageTableState` | all | Pagination + filters + search for server-side DataTable |
| `useQueryError` | all (config differs per app тАФ see apps matrix) | Standardised error / not-found / forbidden rendering for {{STATE_LIB}} |
| `usePermission` | admin (OR-based) / client (AND-based) | Permission checks for conditional UI |
| `useTabUrl` | all | Syncs tab to URL (local variant over `@shared/utils/hooks` if project overrides) |
| `useDialogUrl` | all | Sync dialog open state to URL |
| <fill>       | <fill> | <fill> |

## Rules

- **CRITICAL**: never import a per-app hook from another app. Add a shared
  abstraction if two apps need the same behavior.
- **ENFORCED**: new generic hooks go in `@shared/utils/hooks`; new
  app-specific hooks go in `apps/<app>/src/hooks/`.
- **ENFORCED**: if a per-app hook diverges across apps, document the
  difference in `.agent/context/05-apps-matrix.md`.
